x\in [0,1]
n\rightarrow\infty
\sum_{k=1}^{n}\frac{x^k}{k!}.
\sum_{k=0}^\infty \frac{x^k}{k!}\;\;\text{ is infinite , and this means this series converges for all}\;\;x\in\Bbb R
\begin{align} \lim_{n\rightarrow  \infty}\displaystyle\sum_{k=1}^{n}\frac{x^k}{k!}&=\displaystyle\sum_{k=1}^{\infty}\frac{x^k}{k!}\\& =x+\frac{x^2}{2!}+\frac{x^3}{3!}+\ldots\ldots\\&=e^x-1  \end{align}
